00:00:26.650 --> 00:00:29.120
that this, the measure of
this angle right over here,

00:00:29.120 --> 00:00:31.461
that this is x degrees.

00:00:31.461 --> 00:00:33.410
And so from that, if we
can prove that the measure

00:00:33.410 --> 00:00:36.810
of this opposite angle
is 180 minus x degrees,

00:00:36.810 --> 00:00:38.970
then we've proven that opposite angles

00:00:38.970 --> 00:00:41.590
for an arbitrary quadrilateral
that's inscribed in a circle

00:00:41.590 --> 00:00:44.260
are supplementary, 'cause
if this is 180 minus x,

00:00:44.260 --> 00:00:48.380
180 minus x plus x is
going to be 180 degrees.

00:00:48.380 --> 00:00:50.610
So I encourage you to pause
the video and see if you can do

00:00:50.610 --> 00:00:53.110
that proof and I'll give
