00:00:53.110 --> 00:00:57.390
It's going to involve
the measure of the arcs

00:00:57.390 --> 00:01:00.246
that the various angles intercept.

00:01:00.246 --> 00:01:01.770
So let's think about it a little bit.

00:01:01.770 --> 00:01:06.770
This angle that has a
measure of x degrees,

00:01:06.770 --> 00:01:10.782
it intercepts this arc, so
we see one side of the angle

00:01:10.782 --> 00:01:13.070
goes and intercepts the circle there.

00:01:13.070 --> 00:01:15.630
The other side right over there.

00:01:15.630 --> 00:01:18.280
